## Goal

Add `sentry schema` command that exposes Sentry API endpoint metadata at runtime, enabling AI agents to discover endpoints, parameters, and usage without pre-loaded docs.

## Approach: Build-time Index Generation

Parse `@sentry/api` package at build time to generate a lightweight JSON index (~50-80KB) bundled into the CLI. Three data sources:

1. **`index.js`** â€” function name, HTTP method, URL template (regex: `var NAME = (options) => ...client.METHOD({...url: "..."`)
2. **`sdk.gen.d.ts`** â€” JSDoc descriptions, deprecation status
3. **URL templates** â€” path parameters extracted from `{param_name}` placeholders

