## Schema Index Shape

```typescript
interface ApiEndpoint {
  /** SDK function name: "listAnOrganization_sIssues" */
  fn: string;
  /** HTTP method: "GET" | "POST" | "PUT" | "DELETE" | "PATCH" */
  method: string;
  /** URL template: "/api/0/organizations/{organization_id_or_slug}/issues/" */
  path: string;
  /** Human description from JSDoc */
  description: string;
  /** Path parameters: ["organization_id_or_slug"] */
  pathParams: string[];
  /** Whether endpoint is deprecated */
  deprecated: boolean;
  /** Resource category: "organizations", "projects", "teams", etc. */
  resource: string;
  /** Operation: "list", "retrieve", "create", "update", "delete", etc. */
  operation: string;
}
```

`resource` derived from URL (last non-parameter segment), `operation` from function name verb prefix:
- `/api/0/organizations/{org}/issues/` â†’ resource: `issues`
- `/api/0/issues/{issue_id}/` â†’ resource: `issues`
- `/api/0/projects/{org}/{project}/` â†’ resource: `projects`
- `listAnOrganization_sIssues` â†’ operation: `list`
- `retrieveAnIssue` â†’ operation: `retrieve`
- `createANewProject` â†’ operation: `create`

Operation is the first verb token from the function name: `list`, `retrieve`, `create`, `update`, `delete`, `fetch`, `query`, `add`, `remove`, `bulk*`, `start`, `enable`, `disable`, etc.

## Command Interface

```
sentry schema                    # List all resources (grouped)
sentry schema --list             # List all endpoints (flat)
sentry schema issues             # List endpoints for "issues" resource
sentry schema issues list        # Show specific endpoint details
sentry schema --json             # JSON output of all resources
sentry schema issues list --json # JSON output of specific endpoint
```

## Implementation Steps

### Step 1: Build script (`script/generate-api-schema.ts`)
- Parse `index.js` with regex to extract functionâ†’{method, url} for all 214 endpoints
- Parse `sdk.gen.d.ts` to extract JSDoc descriptions per function
- Extract path params from URL templates (`{param}` â†’ `["param"]`)
- Derive `resource` and `operation` from function names
- Write to `src/generated/api-schema.json`

### Step 2: Runtime loader (`src/lib/api-schema.ts`)
- Import the generated JSON
- Provide query functions: `getAllResources()`, `getEndpointsByResource(name)`, `getEndpoint(resource, operation)`, `searchEndpoints(query)`
- Handle fuzzy matching for resource names

### Step 3: Schema command (`src/commands/schema.ts`)
- Single command with optional positional args `[resource] [operation]`
- `--list` flag for flat endpoint listing
- Human renderer: formatted tables for lists, detailed view for single endpoints
- JSON: passthrough of structured data
- Uses `output: { human: formatSchemaHuman }` pattern (yield CommandOutput)

### Step 4: Register in app.ts
- Add `schema: schemaCommand` to routes

### Step 5: Package scripts
- `generate:schema` â†’ runs `script/generate-api-schema.ts`
- `check:schema` â†’ verifies generated file is up-to-date (for CI)

### Step 6: Tests
- Unit tests for schema query functions
- Integration tests for command output
- Property tests for resource/operation derivation

